		<h3>Will Toaster Wires work on my scooter?</h3>
	</div>
	<div class="grid_8">
		<p>
			Most likely. Toaster Wires have been installed on multiple Honda Ruckus scooters with the stock Honda GET motor, or with GY6 or two-stroke engine swaps. The 20" length of the wire ensures plenty of length to reach from the coil to spark plug, even on scooters running stretch and fatty extensions. Originally developed for the vintage scooter scene, Toaster Wires are also a direct fit to the Genuine Stella and Vespas. It should work most vintage scooters, including Lambrettas. If you're unsure about an application, contact us and we'll try to assist. 
		</p>	
		<p>	
			We do not recommend Toaster Wires for fuel injected engines. Toaster Wires are non-supression spark plug wires and may cause electromagnetic interference. We've never had any reported problems, but please be aware.
		</p>
