	<div class="grid_12"> <h3>How do I install my Toaster Wire?</h3></div>
	<div class="grid_6">
		<p>
			Toaster Wires screw in to your scooter's coil. The old spark plug wire must be removed from the existing coil. Usually this involves the following steps:
			<ol>
				<li>Disconnect the spark plug boot from the spark plug.</li>
				<li>Slide the rubber boot covering where the existing wire meets the existing coil up the existing wire to expose the connection.</li>
				<li>Unscrew the plug wire from the coil. NOTE: Some coils have a small bit of glue holding the wire into the coil. This glue should pop loose easily with a bit of twisting. If the wire will not unscrew from the coil, do not continue twisting the wire. instead, use NGK Part# 8083 to splice the Toaster Wire to your existing wire.</li>
				<li>Remove the rubber boot from the stock wire and slide it over the Toaster Wire.</li>
				<li>Trim the Toaster Wire to length if needed with wire cutters.</li>
				<li>Screw the Toaster Wire into the coil.</li>
				<li>Slide the rubber cover over the connection between the Toaster Wire and the coil.</li>
				<li>Attach the Toaster Wire's boot to the spark plug. </li>
			</ol>
		</p>
	</div>
